<l corresp="72-71"> the manner in which she transformed the sky/heaven/pure-jail-enclosure of the spearman who performed deeds of bravery i.e. violence/warfare [Cōḻa king]/ of the sky-jail-enclosure of the spearman where deeds of bravery i.e. violence/warfare were performed into an enclosure in which dharma is performed; </l>
<l corresp="74">	and (20) the approaching and not withdrawing from the Girl with Choice Jewels </l>
<l corresp="73">	by Viñcaikkāñcaṉaṉ, thinking that [she] was Kāyacaṇṭikai;  </l>
<l corresp="76-75"> and (21) the manner in which Vañcaviñcaiyaṉ kills with [his] strong sword the king's child [Utayakumaraṉ]; </l>
<l corresp="78-77">	and (22) the manner in which she with kohl eyes with red lines of kohl (i.e. the kohl is streaming?) who couldn't bear the sorrow on account of him understood the words (obl. stands for acc here) of the goddess. </l>
<l corresp="80-79">	and (23) the king with the sounding anklets (Māvaṇkiḷḷi)  saying 'Let [the Girl with] Choice Jewels be imprisoned!', and [later] releasing [her];</l>
<l corresp="82"> and (24) the [Girl with] Choice Bangles reaching the land of Āputtiraṉ, </l>
<l corresp="81"> after having talked about good dharma to the [Lady with] the Fragrant Flower Garland [the Cōḻa Queen]; </l>
<l corresp="84"> and (25) the setting out to high Maṇipallavam </l>
<l corresp="83"> by the [Girl with] Ornamental Jewels, after she had gone there with him [Āputtiraṉ];</l>
<l corresp="86-85">	and (26) the manner in which she who had undertaken [this´journey], after taking on the disguise of a man of high penance, reached Vañci with its gold banners; </l>
<l corresp="88"> and (27) her asking religious experts [to tell her] their history, </l>
<l corresp="87"> saying, 'Please tell [me] about the good, flawless meanings!'</l>
<l corresp="90"> and (28) the Flower Creeper entering the great city of Kāñci,</l>
<l corresp="89"> after seeking Aṟavaṇar there with those (i.e.above mentioned) mothers/that mother; </l>
